@node editwindow "Edit window"
   @{b} @{u}Add/Insert/Change@{uu}@{ub}

This window is used to add, insert and change list entries. When 'Ok' is pressed UCT checkes if the id name or id number already exist and if min is greater than max.
To cancel the request close the window.
@endnode

@node use "Usage"
@prev intro
@next menus
   @{b} @{u}How to use Universal Catalog Tool@{uu}@{ub}

To make UCT easy to use there are 'help bubbles' and online guide help.

The GUI consists of a lister gadget and a couple of string gadgets. The lister gadget shows you the list of messages in the catalog. Each list entry contains a number of datafields. The @{"datafields" LINK datafields} are edited from the string gadgets depending on which 'mode' your'e in.

The program is divided into three modes:
@{"Programmer mode" LINK mainwindow_prog}
@{"Translator mode" LINK  mainwindow_tran}
@{"Proofreader mode" LINK  mainwindow_prof}

In order to write a catalog you must fill out the @{"Version" LINK version_group} and @{"Language" LINK language_string} gadgets. You can also supply your own name in the @{"Author" LINK author_string} gadget.

The list is uppdated when scrolling the list with the arrow keys. This means that to submit your changes you MUST press 'up' or 'down'.

UCT has two @{"preview windows" LINK prevwindow} which are updated in realtime.

Finally there is a @{"menu" LINK menus} stuffed with functions.
@endnode

@node datafields
        @{u}@{b}The datafields are:@{uu}@{ub}

        @{b}ID number@{ub} - The number in the catalog.
            Can only be edited in 'Programmer mode'.
            Normally found in a CD file.

        @{b}Min@{ub} - The minimum legth of the message.
            Can only be edited in 'Programmer mode'.
            Normally found in a CD file.

        @{b}Max@{ub} - The maximum legth of the message.
            Can only be edited in 'Programmer mode'.
            Normally found in a CD file.

        @{b}ID name@{ub} - The name of the string.
            Can only be edited in 'Programmer mode'.
            Normally found in a CD file.

       @{b} Original string@{ub} - The string in the original language.
            Can only be edited in 'Programmer mode'.
            Normally found in a CD file.

        @{b}Translated string@{ub} - The translator's work.
            Can be edited in 'Translator mode'
            Normally found in a CT file.

        @{b}Comment@{ub} - Additional comments.
            Can be edited in 'Translator mode'
            Normally found in a CD or CT file.

        @{b}Proofreader's corrected string@{ub} - The proofreader's work
            Can be edited in 'Proofreader mode'
            Normally not found.

       @{b} Proofreader's comment@{ub} - The proofreader's comment
            Can be edited in 'Proofreader mode'
            Normally not found.
@endnode

@node intro "Introduction"
@next use
@prev main
   @{b} @{u}Introduction to Universal Catalog Tool@{uu}@{ub}

UCT is a locale catalog tool with many features (some new). We have targeted catalog creators, translators and proofreaders as users of our program. UCT has a MUI GUI for comfortable usage.

In programmer mode you can edit the catalog from the beginning, add and delete messages. You can also change the id names and max/min limits, which is usually done in a cd file.

In translator mode you can translate a catalog and import corrections from your proofreader.

In proofreader mode you can correct the translators work and save the corrections to a special file.

In all modes you can save your project to a special file, similar to the catalog format, but with additional information. In that way you can test the catalog with locale right away.
@endnode

@node reqs "Requirements"
   @{u}@{b}UCT requires at least:@{uu}@{ub}

    AmigaOS 3.0
    CPU MC68020
    MUI 3.8
@endnode

